title: Larin's amazing rookie campaign continues with brace against NYCFC
text:
Larin's amazing rookie campaign continues with brace against NYCFC Goal.com 11 hrs ago Â© Provided by Goal.com Orlando City forward Cyle Larin is having a rookie season for the ages, and it continued on Friday night.
AdChoices The 20-year-old Canadian scored twice in the second half to keep his team in the playoff race, as Orlando City defeated New York City FC 2-1 in front of 43,179 fans at the Citrus Bowl.
Kwame Watson-Siriboe scored against the run of play just before the half to give the away side the lead, but Larin came to life in the second half. The striker netted a header to equalize in the 62nd minute, before tapping home from an Adrian Winter feed in the 70th minute. The brace took his tally to 17 goals for the season, which has long since smashed the previous rookie goal-scoring record of 11.
With the win, Orlando City pulled to within one point of Montreal for the sixth and final playoff spot in the Eastern Conference. Montreal has two games left in the season, while Orlando now has one game remaining.
